Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). In a large bowl, combine the beef, onion, crushed crackers, salt, ground black pepper, steak sauce, eggs and water and mix well. Transfer to an ungreased 9x13 inch baking dish. Form into a loaf about 6x10 inches. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 1 hour, or until center is completely cooked.